namespace Java.Lang

Contains .NET proxy types for Java classes from the package java.lang.

See:
          Description

Type Summary
Appendable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.Appendable.
An object to which char sequences and values can be appended.
AutoCloseable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.AutoCloseable.
An object that may hold resources (such as file or socket handles) until it is closed.
Boolean .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Boolean.
The Boolean class wraps a value of the primitive type boolean in an object.
Byte .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Byte.
The Byte class wraps a value of primitive type byte in an object.
CharSequence .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.CharSequence.
Character .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Character.
The Character class wraps a value of the primitive type char in an object.
Class .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Class.
Instances of the class Class represent classes and interfaces in a running Java application.
ClassLoader .NET proxy type for class java.lang.ClassLoader.
A class loader is an object that is responsible for loading classes.
ClassNotFoundException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.ClassNotFoundException.
Thrown when an application tries to load in a class through its string name using:
  • The forName method in class Class.
Cloneable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.Cloneable.
A class implements the Cloneable interface to indicate to the java.lang.Object.clone() method that it is legal for that method to make a field-for-field copy of instances of that class.
Comparable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.Comparable.
This interface imposes a total ordering on the objects of each class that implements it.
Double .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Double.
The Double class wraps a value of the primitive type double in an object.
Enum .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Enum.
This is the common base class of all Java language enumeration types.
Exception .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Exception.
The class Exception and its subclasses are a form of Throwable that indicates conditions that a reasonable application might want to catch.
Float .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Float.
The Float class wraps a value of primitive type float in an object.
IllegalAccessException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.IllegalAccessException.
An IllegalAccessException is thrown when an application tries to reflectively create an instance (other than an array), set or get a field, or invoke a method, but the currently executing method does not have access to the definition of the specified class, field, method or constructor.
IllegalArgumentException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.IllegalArgumentException.
Thrown to indicate that a method has been passed an illegal or inappropriate argument.
InstantiationException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.InstantiationException.
Thrown when an application tries to create an instance of a class using the newInstance method in class Class, but the specified class object cannot be instantiated.
Integer .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Integer.
The Integer class wraps a value of the primitive type int in an object.
Iterable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.Iterable.
Long .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Long.
The Long class wraps a value of the primitive type long in an object.
NoSuchFieldException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.NoSuchFieldException.
Signals that the class doesn't have a field of a specified name.
NoSuchMethodException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.NoSuchMethodException.
Thrown when a particular method cannot be found.
Number .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Number.
The abstract class Number is the superclass of platform classes representing numeric values that are convertible to the primitive types byte, double, float, int, long, and short.
NumberFormatException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.NumberFormatException.
Thrown to indicate that the application has attempted to convert a string to one of the numeric types, but that the string does not have the appropriate format.
Object .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Object.
Class Object is the root of the class hierarchy.
Package .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Package.
Package objects contain version information about the implementation and specification of a Java package.
Readable .NET proxy type for interface java.lang.Readable.
A Readable is a source of characters.
ReflectiveOperationException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException.
Common superclass of exceptions thrown by reflective operations in core reflection.
RuntimeException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.RuntimeException.
RuntimeException is the superclass of those exceptions that can be thrown during the normal operation of the Java Virtual Machine.
SecurityException .NET proxy type for class java.lang.SecurityException.
Thrown by the security manager to indicate a security violation.
Short .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Short.
The Short class wraps a value of primitive type short in an object.
String .NET proxy type for class java.lang.String.
The String class represents character strings.
Throwable .NET proxy type for class java.lang.Throwable.
The Throwable class is the superclass of all errors and exceptions in the Java language.
